All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractTile
    AbstractTile class that implements a Tile.
    Acid
    Acid Tile, kills chap on contact.
    Actor
    An actor is a character that can move around and be stored in Tiles, such as Chap and Spider.
    Board  
    Chap
    Chap is the main actor in the game and hence his class is special and contains many unsupported operations.
    Door
    A door is a tile that requires a key to open.
    Exit
    The exit tile is the one chap finishes a level on.
    ExitLock
    The tile that sits just before the exit.
    Free
    The free tile is the most important tile.
    Game
    The Game class is the core of handling the game's logic.
    GUI
    GUI is the origin of the game.
    Info
    The info tile contains tips for the user.
    InfoPanel
    In this class, the panel dedicated to one information of the game is created.
    MainFrame
    In this class, the outfit of the mainFrame is generated and more things are added to it in the GUI class.
    Position
    The Position class represents a location on the maze in terms of row and col number.
    RecordAndPlay  
    RenderTile  
    StartingFrame
    StartingFrame is the initial menu which the user can pick an action.
    Tile
    The tile interface represents a tile in the maze.
    Time
    Time is a tile that gives the user a time bonus upon stepping on it.
    Wall
    The Wall tile is a tile that no actor can walk on.
    XMLSaveLoad
    Contains static methods which save and load a Game object to and from XML.
